                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14509.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-05T15:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1915—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 3, 6 p.m. The matter has been fully discussed with Douglas and
                    Arredondo. The former has seen my representation just prepared as a preliminary
                    statement after conference with them. Have asked for his suggestion regarding
                    relief of situation and have made important the necessity of continuing
                    uninterrupted railroad and telegraph communication with Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
